{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1074/comments/1843953.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1074/_/diff#comment-1843953"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1074, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1074.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1074"}}, "title": "Oculus Rift support"}, "content": {"raw": "On saucy, I get the following warnings from code_check:\n\n\n```\n#!c++\n\n[gazebo/rendering/OculusCamera.cc:560]: (style) The scope of the variable 'cam' can be reduced.\n[gazebo/rendering/OculusCamera.cc:610]: (style) The scope of the variable 'cam' can be reduced.\n\n```\n\nI think you just need to move the declaration of `cam` inside the for loops.\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>On saucy, I get the following warnings from code_check:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">gazebo</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rendering</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">OculusCamera</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nl\">cc</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">560</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">style</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">The</span> <span class=\"n\">scope</span> <span class=\"n\">of</span> <span class=\"n\">the</span> <span class=\"n\">variable</span> <span class=\"err\">&#39;</span><span class=\"n\">cam</span><span class=\"err\">&#39;</span> <span class=\"n\">can</span> <span class=\"n\">be</span> <span class=\"n\">reduced</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">gazebo</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rendering</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">OculusCamera</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nl\">cc</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">610</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">style</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">The</span> <span class=\"n\">scope</span> <span class=\"n\">of</span> <span class=\"n\">the</span> <span class=\"n\">variable</span> <span class=\"err\">&#39;</span><span class=\"n\">cam</span><span class=\"err\">&#39;</span> <span class=\"n\">can</span> <span class=\"n\">be</span> <span class=\"n\">reduced</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>I think you just need to move the declaration of <code>cam</code> inside the for loops.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2014-05-09T20:37:22.031622+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0/ca24bb11-4787-4b14-a20d-d91835e9bde2/128"}}, "nickname": "Nathan Koenig", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0"}, "updated_on": "2014-05-09T20:37:22.039920+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 1843953}